      "description": "Offered is a driver-focused 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six power plant. This high-revving mill utilizes six individual throttle bodies and double-VANOS variable valve timing to deliver linear power up to its 8,000 RPM redline. Power is routed through a precise Getrag 6-speed manual transmission to a factory-calibrated M-Variable differential lock. The chassis maintains its composure with a McPherson strut front and multi-link rear suspension, while the critical rear subframe mounting points have been inspected and reinforced for long-term structural integrity. Recent service includes a valve clearance adjustment and cooling system refresh, ensuring the thermal efficiency of this iconic sports coupe remains optimal for spirited driving.",
